<item>
            <title>[MAHOUT-1238] VectorWritable&apos;s bug with VectorView of sparse vectors</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MAHOUT-1238</link>
                <project id="12310751" key="MAHOUT">Mahout</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;VectorWritable raises an exception if it is used on a VectorView of a sparse vector. The reason is that the sparse vector writes only the non-zero elements, while VectorView&apos;s implementation of getNumNondefaultElements() returns the size of the entire data. Later when reading the vector, VectorWritable expects reading more items that was written.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
